                  <decoDesc>
                    <summary>Miniatures (1 and 10 appear to be older; miniatures 2-9 are in the late twentieth-century hand of the “speckled garment artist,” painted over text</summary>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d01">
                        <locus target="#ir"/>
                        <desc>The Madonna and Child, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነብይ፡ ሙሴ፡ ምስለ፡ ፅላቱ፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d02">
                        <locus target="#iv"/>
                        <desc>Moses with the Tablets of the Law (catalogue has Seated Saint wiht a Book before Mary) <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1024MosesLaw"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንጉስ፡ ነብይ፡ ዳዊት፡, በገና፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d03">
                        <locus target="#5v"/>
                        <desc>David playing the harp, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1066DavidHarp"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንጉስ፡ ነብይ፡ ዳዊት፡, በገና፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d04">
                        <locus target="#56v"/>
                        <desc>The Madonna and Child, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d05">
                        <locus target="#96v"/>
                        <desc>The Crucifixion <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d06">
                        <locus target="#149v"/>
                        <desc>Jesus Carrying the Cross, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1065RoadtoCalvary"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዚእነ።እየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዝከመ፡ እርኡተ፡ መውቀሉ፡ ጽመ፡, አይሁድ፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d07">
                        <locus target="#150r"/>
                        <desc>The Last Supper, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1067LastSupper"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ምሠተ፡ ሐሙስ።</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d08">
                        <locus target="#150v"/>
                        <desc>The Burial of Jesus  <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1010Entombment"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d09">
                        <locus target="#151r"/>
                        <desc>Jesus Raises Adam and Eve, <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1008Descent"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝከመ፡ ተንሠአ፡ እሙታን፡ አመ፡ ሣልስት፡ ዕለት፡, አዳም አቡነ፡, እግዚእነ፡ እየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡, ሔዋን፡ እምነ፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10">
                        <locus target="#151v"/>
                        <desc>The Holy Trinity <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1030Trinity"/> with caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">አጋዝዕተ፡ የመል፡ መልዕተ፡ ፍጡራ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጻገዖት፡ ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ለአብ፡ ሃሌ፡ ሉያ፡ ለወልድ፡ ሃሉ።ሉያ፡ ለመንፈስቅዱስ፡ ፫፡ ፩፡</foreign>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="d11">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #74v #80r #92v #104v"/> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using Green, Red and Brown);
                      <locus target="#6r"/> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using red, brown and yellow);.
                      <locus target="#26v #49r #119v #137r"/> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign>using black and red);
                      <locus target="#107v"/> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using black, yellow and green);
                      <locus target="#12v #19r #26r #36v #43v #104r #113r #119r #130v #139r #140v #142v #143v #144v #145r"/> (dotted line using alternating black and red);
                      <locus target="#92r"/> (line of pairs of black and red dots);
                      <locus target="#137v"/> (red line)
                    </decoNote>
                    </decoDesc>
                    <additions>
                      <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <desc>
                              <locus target="#62v"/> Marginal note at 78:14 indicating the point “half” of the way through the Psalms: <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈቁ፡ ላዕለ፡ ወመንፈቁ፡ ታሕተ።</foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                          <desc>Isolated names are written on many folios in crude hands</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                          <desc>Two names are given as the copyists: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</foreign>, <locus target="#79v"/>,
                          <locus target="#92r #104r #119r"/> and passim)</desc>
                          and <foreign xml:lang="gez">አስራት፡</foreign>, <locus target="#119r"/> (possibly for <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብራ፡ ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>,
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                          <desc>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#148r"/>); and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#57v #91r"/>)</desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">
                          <desc>The general condition of the vellum is unworn and clean</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <desc>This scribe regularly has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room for the
                            width of most lines. When a line is too long, the scribe places the material above
                            (e.g., <locus target="#6r #7v #11r #14v #16v"/>, etc.) or below (<locus target="#91r"/>) the line</desc>
                        </item>
                      </list>
                    </additions>
